# Scripts Guide

Utility scripts are located in the [scripts/](mdc:scripts) directory.

*   **[scripts/generate_context_map.sh](mdc:scripts/generate_context_map.sh):** Aggregates recent content (last 7 days of AI news, latest weekly/monthly GitHub stats & summaries) from specific subdirectories into a daily JSON file (`the-council/YYYY-MM-DD.json`). Triggered by [.github/workflows/generate_daily_context.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/generate_daily_context.yml).
*   **[scripts/tweet-summarizer.sh](mdc:scripts/tweet-summarizer.sh):** Takes a GitHub activity log file (daily or weekly) as input, uses a prompt ([scripts/prompts/elizaOS.txt](mdc:scripts/prompts/elizaOS.txt) or [scripts/prompts/autofun_prompt.txt](mdc:scripts/prompts/autofun_prompt.txt)) and the OpenRouter API (Claude 3.7 Sonnet by default) to generate a tweet summary. Saves the output to the `tweets/` directory. Triggered by [.github/workflows/tweet-generator.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/tweet-generator.yml).
*   **[scripts/summarize.sh](mdc:scripts/summarize.sh):** A general-purpose summarization script using OpenRouter. It can process text, markdown, JSON (including Whisper format), and MP3 files (requires `insanely-fast-whisper`). It takes an input file and an optional prompt (or prompt file) to generate a summary.
*   **[scripts/process_daily_context.sh](mdc:scripts/process_daily_context.sh):** Reads the aggregated `the-council/daily.json` file, extracts all content, and runs it through specified prompts from [scripts/prompts/](mdc:scripts/prompts) using the [scripts/summarize.sh](mdc:scripts/summarize.sh) script. Saves outputs to [scripts/output/](mdc:scripts/output).
*   **Supporting Files:**
    *   [scripts/brand-guide.txt](mdc:scripts/brand-guide.txt): Contains branding guidelines, likely used in prompts.
    *   [scripts/openrouter-docs.txt](mdc:scripts/openrouter-docs.txt): Documentation for the OpenRouter API.
    *   [scripts/prompts/](mdc:scripts/prompts): Directory containing prompt templates used by summarization scripts.
